On this day: Bitcoin is born. Satoshi Nakamoto launches the Bitcoin network and mines the genesis block, in which he embeds a title from the British newspaper, The Times: "The Times 03/Jan/2009 Chancellor on brink of second bailout for banks".

The first ever Bitcoin transaction was made. On this day, Satoshi Nakamoto, the pseudonymous creator of the Bitcoin system, sent Hal Finney, a well-regarded cryptographer and computer scientist, 10 bitcoin!
Laszlo Hanyecz made the first real-world BTC transaction by buying two pizzas from Papa Johns in Jacksonville, Florida, for 10,000 BTC! That would be worth over $230 million if held until early 2023.

A major vulnerability was found in the bitcoin protocol, permitting a user to create arbitrary amounts of Bitcoin. The vulnerability was exploited, but very soon after this it was fixed and the blockchain was forked to exclude the fraudulent transaction.

A major vulnerability found on August 6 was exploited; A single transaction spent 0.5 bitcoin to send just over 92 billion bitcoins to two different addresses on the network. However, within hours, the transaction was seen, the vulnerability was fixed, and the blockchain was forked to exclude the fraudulent transaction. The fraudulent transaction no longer appears in the blockchain used by the Bitcoin network today. This was the only major security flaw found and exploited in bitcoin's history!

Satoshi Nakamoto, the mysterious, pseudonymous creator of Bitcoin sent a farewell email to a fellow Bitcoin developer: “I’ve moved on to other things,” he wrote, assuring that the future of Bitcoin was “in good hands.” He has not been heard from since...
The US authorities seized accounts associated with Mt. Gox, a Bitcoin exchange based in Japan, after discovering that it had not registered as a money transmitter with FinCEN in the US.

The Bitcoin blockchain splits into two derivative digital currencies, the bitcoin (BTC) chain with 1 MB blocksize limit, and the Bitcoin Cash (BCH) chain with an 8 MB blocksize limit. This split is knows as the "Bitcoin Cash hard fork".
